1. Do not deploy directly to production environment, only deploy to preview environment for debugging and testing
2. Do not commit code to GitHub unless human approval is obtained
3. Do not modify existing styles casually unless human approval is obtained
4. Do not treat symptoms instead of root causes, maintain a global perspective and understand problems at the architectural level
5. Do not modify configuration files casually unless human approval is obtained
6. After completing each feature modification, output a summary document in md format and save it to the local tmp directory, and add tmp directory to .gitignore
7. Always consider mobile-friendly styles, not high priority but affects SEO, so needs consideration
8. Use pnpm, not npm or yarn
9. Before deployment, clean up temporary files, test files, and intermediate build artifacts, then package after cleanup is complete